`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The "JSX runtime chain breaks .tsx tests" MEMORY pattern is critical here — pure functions must live in a `.ts` file separate from the `.tsx` component, so tests don't drag in `react-native-css-interop`
- Camera-center raycast for ghost positioning is the standard FPS building pattern (Minecraft/Fallout 4): cast a ray forward from the camera, snap the hit point to a coarse grid
- The kitbashing `KitbashRapierWorld`/`KitbashRapierModule` minimal interfaces mean we can cast the real Rapier objects without importing the full library into the pure-function layer
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
