`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The `useRapier()` hook must be called at component level (Rules of Hooks), not inside `useFrame`. Store its results in stable refs as shown in the TerrainChunk pattern: `const { rapier, world: rapierWorld } = useRapier();`
- Q/E rotation needs `document.addEventListener` in a `useEffect` — same cleanup pattern as `useMouseLook`. The touch variant can reuse the existing overlay UI buttons
- The ghost Y position from `castRay` hit point should NOT be snapped to a full integer — terrain is continuous. Only X/Z grid-snap is needed for horizontal alignment; Y stays at the hit point
